Enable or disable transparency. **Transparency is disabled by default.**

{:.alert.alert-error}
Be sure to render all non-transparent objects first. Otherwise the color
blending will be off. 

Generally, when rendering with transparency your display function will be
structured like this:

 * disable transparency, enable lighting, set material properties, etc.
 * draw all opaque objects
 * enable transparency, turn off lighting, set color poperties
 * draw all transparent objects

### syntax

~~~ python
transparency(enable)
~~~

### parameters

enable | `True` or `False`

### examples

#### draw a transparent sphere


<%= vroom_example_image "core", "transparency", "draw-a-transparent-sphere.png" %>


~~~ python
def display():
   lighting(False)

   color(0.0, 1.0, 0.0)
   sphere(5.0)

   transparency(True)
   color(0.0, 1.0, 0.0, 0.3)
   sphere(5.0, style="solid")
~~~
